sentence: Among the underlying components of the S&P 500 index, we saw noteworthy options trading volume today in Intuitive Surgical Inc (Symbol: ISRG), where a total of 17,305 contracts have traded so far, representing approximately 1.7 million underlying shares.
That amounts to about 202.4% of ISRG's average daily trading volume over the past month of 855,100 shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $540 strike call option expiring October 19, 2018 , with 1,115 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 111,500 underlying shares of ISRG.

Hasbro, Inc. (Symbol: HAS) saw options trading volume of 11,899 contracts, representing approximately 1.2 million underlying shares or approximately 112% of HAS's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 1.1 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $93.50 strike put option expiring October 26, 2018 , with 1,786 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 178,600 underlying shares of HAS.

Below is a chart showing HAS's trailing twelve month trading history, with the $93.50 strike highlighted in orange:

And Procter & Gamble Company (Symbol: PG) options are showing a volume of 82,777 contracts thus far today.
That number of contracts represents approximately 8.3 million underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 100.5% of PG's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 8.2 million shares.

Particularly high volume was seen for the $92.50 strike call option expiring November 16, 2018 , with 14,160 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 1.4 million underlying shares of PG.
